description:
Anne Waldman lecture on William S. Burroughs's cut-up method
MP3 64kbps 2h5m
Date: 1985-07-23
Label / Recorded by: Jack Kerouac School of Disembodied Poetics

Anne Waldman lecture on the use of the cut-up technique in the work of William S. Burroughs, tracing it from its early development through his later work. She reads from Burroughs's writing and an interview with him in The Paris Review, plays his cut-up tapes, and talks about how Burroughs extended the idea of cut-ups beyond writing to a way of understanding the universe in magical and mystical terms.

